      "intramuscular_fat_and_insulin_resistance": "Excess dietary fat (particularly SFA from trans fats and excess omega-6 PUFA) stored as intramuscular triglycerides (IMTG) → diacylglycerol (DAG) and ceramide accumulation in muscle → serine phosphorylation of IRS-1 (insulin receptor substrate) → blocks PI3K-Akt signalling → skeletal muscle insulin resistance.",
