      "carbohydrate_to_energy_gateway": "Because PDH requires B1, every gram of carbohydrate consumed requires thiamine to be converted to ATP. High carbohydrate diets without adequate B1 produce a relative thiamine deficiency state — glucose accumulates as pyruvate/lactate instead of entering the TCA cycle."
